      "text": [
        " \"لِلْعَيْنِ مَا رَأَتْ وَ لِلْيَدِ مَا أَخَذَتْ \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3431 - Al-Sakuni narrated from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) from his father, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), from his forefathers, from Imam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as):\nHe (as) was asked about a man who saw a bird and followed it until it landed on a tree. Then another man came and took it.\nImam Ali ibn Abi Talib (as) said: \"What the eye sees belongs to it, and what the hand takes belongs to it.\""
        ]
      }
